    {
      "id": "PopularPost72947",
      "post_content": "Okay this is probably worse than lightning bolt. Searing Blaze, Staggershock, and Lightning Bolt are probably all better, but this is the 4th best burn spell in standard, and still highly viable. I can't wrap my head around how some people don't understand how good this card is. Shock is really good removal in the early game when most creatures have two or less toughness. Then, in the late game, this deals 4 dmg. This enables red to take care of four toughness creatures, which it often has trouble doing. Or conversely, go the face. That's 3 viable options on one card (shock a creature, four to a creature, four to the face), the only option that probably won't be used is 2 to the face. There is a ton of versatility in the card. ",
      "posted_by": "ZursApprentice",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost72947\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_post\">Okay this is probably worse than lightning bolt.  Searing Blaze, Staggershock, and Lightning Bolt are probably all better, but this is the 4th best burn spell in standard, and still highly viable.  I can't wrap my head around how some people don't understand how good this card is.   Shock is really good removal in the early game when most creatures have two or less toughness.  Then, in the late game, this deals 4 dmg.  This enables red to take care of four toughness creatures, which it often has trouble doing.  Or conversely, go the face.  That's 3 viable options on one card (shock a creature, four to a creature, four to the face), the only option that probably won't be used is 2 to the face.  There is a ton of versatility in the card.    </span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '72947'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy1466\">ZursApprentice</span>\r\n                                (5/13/2010 12:31:14 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\